1. Introduction: A Methodological Reorientation—Myth as Raw Cognitive Encoding

1.1 The Problem: Structural Homology in Global Creation Myths

For a long time, academia has treated creation myths as fictional products of primitive thought. However, when we adopt the working hypothesis that “all creation myths share a common physical event prototype” and re‑examine a large body of global creation narratives, a striking structural homology emerges:

